# Undercrypt: Hero's Descent - Game Info

## Game Overview
- **Type:** Solo deck-building dungeon crawler (inspired by Slay the Spire, Magic the Gathering)
- **Players:** 1 (future: co-op/PvP)
- **Goal:** Choose a hero, build your deck, clear all dungeon floors, defeat the final boss.

## Core Gameplay Loop
1. **Choose Hero** (4 unique classes)
2. **Start with a 30-card deck** (themed to hero)
3. **Explore dungeon floors** (3 floors, each with themed monsters, rooms, and bosses)
4. **Combat:**
   - Turn-based: Draw → Action → Enemy → End
   - Play cards using energy (3 per turn)
   - Defeat monsters, survive enemy turns
5. **Progression:**
   - Gain XP, level up (more HP, new cards, upgraded abilities)
   - Collect loot: new cards, relics (passives), healing, gold
   - Build and refine deck (add/remove cards, upgrade)
6. **Victory:** Defeat all bosses. **Defeat:** Hero HP reaches 0.

## Hero Classes
- **Knight of Ashes (Warrior):** Tank, armor/block, heavy attacks
- **Shadowmancer (Rogue):** Poison, card draw, curses
- **Frost Witch (Mage):** Freeze, spell synergy, AoE
- **Beast Tamer (Summoner):** Summons, healing, support

Each hero has:
- HP, hand size, starting deck
- Passive ability (always on)
- Active ability (costs energy, cooldown)

## Card System
- **Types:** Attack, Defense, Spell, Summon, Relic
- **Properties:** Cost (energy), effects (damage, block, heal, poison, freeze, etc.), rarity, element, tags
- **Deck:** 18–30 cards, built over run
- **Sample Card:**
  - Knight's Strike (Attack, 1 energy, Deal 6 damage)
  - Defend (Defense, 1 energy, Gain 5 block)
  - Flame Burst (Spell, 2 energy, Deal 8 AoE damage)

## Dungeon & Monsters
- **Floors:**
  1. Vermin Nest (rats, spiders, Rat King boss)
  2. Forgotten Crypt (skeletons, wraiths, Lich boss)
  3. Dark Core (demons, cultists, Dungeon Overlord boss)
- **Room Types:** Combat, Elite, Boss, Treasure, Shop
- **Monster Types:** Minion, Elite, Boss (unique abilities, HP, attacks)

## Turn Structure
1. **Draw Phase:** Draw to hand size
2. **Action Phase:** Play cards (spend energy)
3. **Enemy Phase:** Monsters attack, trigger abilities
4. **End Phase:** Discard, apply ongoing effects

## Progression & Loot
- **XP:** Defeat enemies, level up (HP, new cards, abilities)
- **Loot:** New cards, relics, healing, gold
- **Deckbuilding:** Add/remove/upgrade cards, synergy bonuses

## Data & Types (see `/types` and `/data`)
- **Card:** id, name, type, cost, description, effects[], element, rarity, tags
- **Hero:** id, name, class, HP, handSize, startingDeck[], passive/active abilities
- **Monster:** id, name, type, HP, attack, abilities[], loot, xpReward
- **Room/Floor:** id, name, description, rooms[] (combat, boss, shop, etc.)

## Main Engine Functions (see `lib/game-engine.ts`)
- `loadGameData(cards, heroes, monsters)`
- `startGame(heroId)`
- `startTurn()`
- `playCard(index, target)`
- `enemyTurn()`
- `applyEffects()`
- `processStatusEffects()`
- `drawToHandSize()`
- `shuffleDeck()`

## Example Data (see `/data/*.json`)
- **Card:**
  ```json
  { "id": "knight_strike", "name": "Knight's Strike", "type": "Attack", "cost": 1, "effects": [{ "type": "damage", "value": 6, "target": "enemy" }], ... }
  ```
- **Hero:**
  ```json
  { "id": "knight_of_ashes", "name": "Knight of Ashes", "class": "Warrior", "baseHP": 80, "handSize": 5, "startingDeck": [ ... ], ... }
  ```
- **Monster:**
  ```json
  { "id": "giant_rat", "name": "Giant Rat", "type": "Minion", "hp": 25, "attack": 8, "abilities": [ ... ], ... }
  ```
- **Floor:**
  ```json
  { "id": "vermin_nest", "name": "Vermin Nest", "rooms": [ ... ] }
  ```

## For Developers
- **Add new cards/heroes/monsters** by editing JSON in `/data` and updating types in `/types`.
- **Game logic** is in `lib/game-engine.ts` (see methods above).
- **UI**: React/Next.js in `/app` and `/components`.

